\alpha + \theta = \beta
1. \, BE = EF = FC = AB
2. \, \angle AEB = \beta , \angle AFB = \alpha , \angle ACB = \theta. 
1. \cos\beta =  \sin \beta
2.\cos\alpha = 2\sin\alpha
3. \cos \theta = 3\sin \theta
\tan\beta=2\tan\alpha=3\tan\theta
\begin{align} \tan(\alpha+\theta)&=\frac{\tan\alpha+\tan\theta}{1-\tan\alpha\tan\theta}\\ &=\frac{\frac56\tan\beta}{1-\frac{\tan^2\beta}6}\\ &=\frac{5\tan\beta}{6-\tan^2\beta} \end{align}
6-\tan^2\beta=5
\tan\beta=1
\beta=45^\circ
\beta= 45degree
\tan(\alpha + \theta)
(\tan\alpha+\tan\theta)
1-\tan\alpha\tan\theta =
\tan\beta
1-\tan^2\beta
5\tan\beta
6-\tan^2\beta
\tan(\alpha + \theta)=1=\tan\beta
\alpha + \theta = \beta
